\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Do you think that's because you were a girl, if you'd been a boy would you have gone on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Well - no. You see, in these
 days - well - I left - I left the school - and I think that the - my grandfather was living here on his own and my father and - well - and I left the school, I got no option, I was sent to - work at my - keep to help my grandfather, to help - with his wo
r
k. It was a sort of service which - I think it was terrible you know that. It wasna right. And my grandfather employed, me, give me three pound ten a half year, I used to get this wage. Well, I thought - it was a - it wasnae right. To do that. No, and my 
f
ather's - he should have said - I should have been sent - why I don't know. But - because I wasnae a dumbcock, I know I wasnae. And he sent me - I was to come up here to work to my grandfather, three pound ten a half year. Well I'd no training, an odd bit
 
of - wash the floors and wash the dishes and - and do that sort of thing, but I wasna trained. One then - he didna pay me - he only gave me the once - paid me the week after that, he'd be thinking that was - half a crown a week was plenty for me, I got tw
o and six a week for all that. Needles to say I used to always have my bath here, 'cos he had a good bath here. And the boys used to come up here of their bath. And - so I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Did he have a proper bathroom here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Oh up here, a splendid bathroom.
 This was the only house in the district that had a bathroom. And needless to say - a hundred years ago, this was the only house - and that cottage type house there, there wasnae another house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Queen Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. This is - that - these are close - that street there, that terrace, they were there. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15487441\charrsid10313804 apostolic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804  church was there, and - right - and the Catholic school in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Shakespeare Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was there. There was no Brook Street, there was no houses, nothing in the Hood's Loaning, nothing in Leafield Road, nothing i
n Queen Street, nothing - there was nothing anywhere here, a hundred years ago, but allotments. 'Cos when I think a hundred years back - but you know - but where the elastic works is now in Leafield Road, that was - I can - that - that - now electricity s
tarted about 1902 or 3 or something like - they start working there then. That was allotments. And there was a burn, there was a burn run through that. Nice ground, they were nice gardens there. All round the Hood's Loaning then. See?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 So this house was something special round about here?
