Well, this - my grandfather built that one in the front here. That was the first one he built. And it was too big. And he bought - the ground and built this - this house. So these were the only - at that, but all these - in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Queen Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, there was nothing - nothing in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cumberland Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Nothing anywhere. And I could remember when - and in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bruges Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} there would be nothing. There was nothing. Nothing in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bruges Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15487441\charrsid10313804 Michaels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804  church. And I could remember - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Murray Place{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, opposite - you know where the Gas is, big gate is - at the corner. Well these were all built, I remember this being built. And it was a hollow ground there. You run down a bank and in there you see. When you come down to foot of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Queen Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} y
ou're very low down, you're nearly as low as in a hole. You see, you're coming down hill to - right down the hill on the road. And - in - at the bottom of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Brooms Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, where the - where the - the Gas House is - was, in there, it was a - a bank and you ran down the bank and there - it was like -
