\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Who gave you the belt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
That's another thing that happened to me. These are - well - to me as I would say a private thing again. We were on holiday. And - at - our mother's - step-mother's mother, we were on holiday. Now - I wonder wh
at age I would be. I wouldna be that - old. But - we were away to bed and it was a summertime, we were away to bed, and - and - I had this wee bed to myself. Now, you ken, in the summer - nice warm summer night it's difficult for - for kids to - get to sl
e
ep, and remember getting up and looking at the things on the dressing table, well Aunt Jenny had a - well there was things people prize in these days. She had a chocolate box. And I used to take lid, and smell it, you could smell the rich - it was a nice,
 
it had been a gift. It was empty you know but she'd kept it. And I remember smelling this box. And - and then I put the lid on, and then - she'd a wee watch - a watch, I stand and I'm watching it, and I can remember taking - lifting the watch and listenin
g
 to it. And - and then I thought I heard somebody coming up the stair and I jumped into bed because I knew I shouldn't have got out of bed. Watch and I went into bed, and I pretended I was sleeping. Well - mother had said - so of course I told a lie. That
'
s another thing, you told lies to save your skin. I did. I suppose - we were rode to it. I wasnae. And of course whether she missed the watch I don't know, but - whether she missed the watch or not I don't know, whether she turned - I don't know, but she 
d
iscovered me with the watch in my hand. Oh I got - she'd a strap, and she took this - strap, and it was a strap for strapping a basket, a - a luggage strap, and I got belted around the bedroom with this strap. And - well - I never forgot that. And then fo
r
 the rest of that holiday - I think I would be in the bad books. I can remember - I got leave to - I wonder if that was - there - there was another night that I got leave to get up, wanted something. Now - as I say, we told lies. You can make a liar. You 
can make a child a liar. Used to tell lies to save your skin, and of course one lie leads to another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 And you end up with a hammering at the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Aye, well - I remember this day, there was a family up the road. That I would stop - a lot of girls
 in them, and their father was a coachman at the big house, and I got to know these girls and - and - they - used to come down and I'd been - I hadna - I hadna to play with the Byers you see. However the girls had came down and I'd been with the Byers's a
n
d we wandered away up a road, a country - it was in the country, we wandered up the road. Now I knew my mother and the - and my two brothers were picking rasps - in the hedge, I know they were picking rasps. And - so they were on the cross road, we were g
o
ing - this. And - said - so I said, well I - I kept - I made - and I had to tell them that - I - I didna want her to see - see me with them you see. So - we all - we all - we all joined hands and run across together and she'll never see. So we did that of
 course, of course she'd seen us right enough. And well I got a hammering for that. For being with the Byers's. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15487441\charrsid10313804 be sent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804  - not remember what I was sent to bed for. However this aunt - this aunt was servant somewhere near and she come in this night and of
 coursed she said to let me get up so I got - but you felt like a culprit. You - you were allowed to get up and you sat there, a culprit. Now that would be before the - no I couldnae have been that much old because that was - that would be before 19 - 19 
- 1896, so that might have been 1894 or '95 you see, '94. So - that were the age of me but - but I - well you never forgot that hammering. Not -
