Oh well - I remember about that - that one, I think that would be the first Christmas. That would be the - the - the first Christmas - t
hat might have been the first Christmas that she was our step-mother that we got these presents. Mine was the Child Magazine and John got the trumpet and Jim got something. I know - I think so, I think that would be the first Christmas. That I remember. O
h
 well, somehow these things - always stuck, these - the belts. Oh you could never forget. And funny, as I grew older and that I thought, well - and - in later years when I come to - to - oh she died you see, and - the aunts, well they were - they were kin
d, they were nice and they kept a cow and they were nice. I made up my mind well, I'll make it up to them, I'll be good to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
