Well - well you see, up - latterly - latterly - there's plenty of Catholics and Protestants have go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9572179\charrsid10313804 t married. But - a good Catholic\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 ll no marry a Protestant. If he's a good
 Catholic. Because - again, if he's a good Protestant - he might - although I don't - in cases - a good Catholic'll no marry a Protestant. And if he's a good Protestant - well I've known - Protestants that did but it's generally - the wife that's the - so
rt of - kind of - well, not always - no, I couldnae say, a really good Protestant, true to his - he's true to his religion as the Catholic ever departing from it. Now you could say that yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Did you have any special reason for choosing to be married on Christmas Day?

