Possibly it would be a holiday, I don't know why I was married on Christmas Day. It would be - I think - but you see - Christmas wasn't made so much of in these days as what New Year was, in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. In that time we - now Christmas - Christmas Day is much more in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} as it was then. New Year - New Year Day, that was the - that was the - great feast day in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And they - later - they - in the '80's and before - Scotland held New Year's Day far more, they didn't held - 
they didn't hold Christmas Day very much. Well I think it would be - it would be - a holiday like then. It would be a closed day, there'd be a reason but - but - again, it was - you could have a nice Christmas dinner and - I really can't remember why - my
 father would have to do with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Was it your father who paid for the wedding?
