se, it was twenty-two pounds, and the - and - from then on of course - we'd to - the deposit - make - put a deposit in the bank. That's what - I went to the bank with a lot of money - I never was a spender. When we hadna got it. That I always - I was aye 
-
 what little money I had I kept. For the rainy day, so that - what little I had was on deposit and - it wasnae a great deal but it was put in the bank. Therefore we got that in the bank and that allowed us - to - to - buy what we needed to stat the shop, 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9572179\charrsid10313804 you needed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
 tools and you needed scales, you needed - tremendous things, well we needed a horse. The first thing we needed was the horse. That was the first thing, so how ever - we never needed to draw on our - that was our security. We never needed to - to 
