Teaching music. And - the two - they were maiden ladies. One was a - they were both Irish. Well they were Roman Catholics, I don't know what they've been Irish but - Morgan, I think that - it looks like an Irish name, but - the elder - the two
 - the more proficient - the one what was the organist - she was an awful nice creature. But they lived round there, poor things, they had - they hadnae - a meagre existence. She'd plenty of peoples - and - I think - I think a guinea was her fee. Whether 
a
 guinea was a quarter or what but it was something like that. But they had a precarious livelihood. And they were - one sister kept the house, and they kept a - a day girl to - a maid they called her, but she's just a day girl. When they had anybody. And 
-
 the other sister - the elder of the two that was the principle, she was - ever so nice but Miss Cecilia was - erratic. And, you know, oh - it was pathetic, their existence. They hadna much to work on. Poor. But they wouldn't have admitted they were poor.
 They lived in a - Knightsbrook House, a nice house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Shakespeare Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. But - they would get a wee girl used to come in and go - go messages for them, I'm saying they had - they had somebody, I think somebody come in and did a wee bit of work for them bu
