\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Do you remember anything special about any of the elections here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
No, I can't say - there's only one thing that I - regret and was wrong. You - you wouldna remember anything about prohibition do you? Prohibition. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9572179\charrsid10313804 Well}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804  it was - aye, well,
 you see, it was greatly on at the time. It's funny that - that's so long ago but I've thought about it many times, well - you see, that - the church that we were - Martyr's church, as I say, the - the - the wife just took a wee bit more - to do than she 
s
hould have done. Now they were keen on this prohibition you see. Well - you'd to sign this prohibition paper, you - you'd to sign for prohibition. And - well I was quite safe - 'cos you saw the drunkenness across the road, pubs and - and he saw what drunk
e
ness these people - spend money on drink and - and - land - and what it - how degrading it is. And he felt well - the only way you could see was that - to do away with the drink. Well you ken that - that - that's the wrong attitude. There - nobody has any
 right to interfere, if - if it was wrong, the Government should have seen to things but - that shouldn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9572179\charrsid10313804 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804  be left to the individual. But of course that - you can see that now but - well of course our minister's wife was keen for us - all to sign this prohibi
tion. Well I had no hesitation in signing it. And of course I encouraged my husband to sign it. Now - one of his customers was a publican.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 And did he find out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Of course the names were there to be seen. Well - that - was wrong. And he - you know
, knowing my husband, the kind of man he was, he - now he did it to please me you ken, he - he did it to please me. And of course when he went for his order this day she told him - she didna want anything. Well it was wrong that. I thought well it was wro
n
g to make him - to get Willie - Willie did it because I - thought we should do it, but there again - now - there were nobody pushing it down their throats, they bought it and - and if the country said well it was so, well - you'd nothing. Well now, we wer
e
na the only one. Because I remember a grocer telling me - how he had signed. And he had lost some of his custom. He thought he - well he thought he was doing what was right, you see. He saw the - the - the evils of the drink. And that he would - he would 
supply maybe - maybe some of the folk that were drinking were owing him money. You see? But - that wasnae going to cure it. You see. That wasnae going to cure it, prohibition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Did you ever go out much of an evening at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Never. No, we'd no soc
ial - we'd no social life. No, he - he - and again - and there wasna much time and then - and then he - he was a - a husband, and I remember once - being invited up to the Manse. Well I had to decline. However the minister was a - he was decent. He come d
own and he asked me, and he said was it Willie. I said, well just come yourself. He knew that - he knew that - and - that - Willie wasnae a - a mixer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Did you ever go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Very rarely. Very rarely. Only once in a while. Again werena a
 great deal of time for that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Did you have problems about baby sitting if you had wanted to go out to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
We - once - now, I had a cousin staying with me here. And - she said - now at this time - well I - I'd always a youn
g - I'd a girl help me in the house and she - she lived in. And - well we werena keen but she was, she says, oh, she says, you go - we were to go to this - play, and she was staying with - she would stay in. I didna take advantage - of the girl. The girl 
w
as quite trustworthy, that if we' wanted to go she could have looked after them but - I don't suppose we would be in the habit of doing that but - a cousin would - she would - she would stay in and - look after Willie. So - we went. Of course Willie must 
h
ave sensed that - that we were out. You see. And - he was the only one. He must have sensed that we were out and therefore he didna sleep. You see, he was unsettled. And - of course she told me that he hadna slept and all that sort of thing. But next day 
-
 the wee lassie was fair annoyed. She says, Auntie Hetty smacked him. Oh - Auntie Hetty - of course she was a part time nursemaid at where she - where she was - where she was working. She was a part time nursemaid to a wee girl. She was - she was annoyed.
 She says, Auntie Hetty smacked him. So I said now that's the first and the only time, I'll never go out again. Never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 You had a girl living in with you, when did you first get her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Well I got the - I got the girl - you see, my father made it
 a condition that if I stayed here - and - kept house I was to get a girl in to help me with the work. And well - when he - died, I had got this wee girl, she'd come - a few weeks before he died. And she would be with me five years. Quite a nice }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9572179\charrsid10313804 lassie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 . An
d - oh she - more or less kept in touch with that family for - oh, many many years. As - Emmie was here about five years, and then I think as the war got on - and that - well she was due to - she should go away and get more money but - but - for some reas
o
n - well really I hadnae the money but there was some reason, I did without her. And she went away and got another job but - but - she was quite happy. So when - when - she was quite young, she'd just left the school, when she came to me she'd just left t
h
e school. And her mother brought her and - and - and - she used to - to say how she lived - she lived just outside town a wee bit, she used to go away after tea to play and come back in to sleep at night again. She could - she could - get home for - a nig
ht. She had days out, nights out, but she could get home at night to play and - she'd be back in at night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Did you sort of treat her as one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Well - not altogether, no, I think she would - I think she would have her food as far as m
ind I think - no, I think we'd all our food together. But I cannae just remember that. You can't always do that because they could hear things, I can't remember much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 But she had a fair amount of time off then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Oh she was quite happy here, she would learn to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 What sort of jobs would she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Oh well, she would mind Willie and - oh I canna tell you, she was just - just generally help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Did she call you Mrs Sturgeon and what would you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Oh I expect - Emmie. She was just Emmie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 You had other girls then after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Oh I had several - many - lots of girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Did they all sleep in here too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 No. I think Emmie was the only one that slept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 What sort of money did you have to pay for a girl to live in in those days?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Well I really can't remember. Can't remember what they got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 It probably wouldn't be all that much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 I could not tell you, I can't remember what they got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 She was a nice girl and you got on quite well with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 She was a nice girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Would she do quite a lot for Willie when he was wee? Would she put him to bed or would you do these things yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Oh she could - well I can't remember - really canna remember but - oh she got on quite well with Willie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 What did he call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Emmie. Oh I got on quite well with Emmie. I must tell you an incident. After Emmie went and then we'd started the shop - Emmie had got away and - then - we'd heard - as I say, I kept more or less in touch with the family all th
ough their life and all through their lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Once you had your own household in here did you see very much of your relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 Well you see, we had very few - we had very few relations. Very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid556246 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 There would be your husband's mother while she was still alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6565549 WS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16322180\charrsid10313804 
Oh well she lived quite near, granny, they were - they were about, they popped in - out and in, you see.
